Perseus is an agentless endpoint technology focused on saving incident responders time and detecting persistent malware that is missed by existing technologies. Perseus allows you to detect, visualize, and remediate unauthorized persistence in your organization. Please go to https://www.PerseusSec.com for more info.

The Perseus Splunk App provides the user interface for Perseus. It must be used in conjunction with the Perseus Engine. The Perseus Engine provides a wizard for integrating Perseus with your existing techologies to gather forensic data, eliminating the need to deploy additional agents in your environment. That forensic data is processed by Perseus and presented in the Perseus Splunk App to save incident responders time and to detect malware missed by other technologies. Please go to https://www.PerseusSec.com/download to download the Perseus Engine. 

For assistance, please email Perseus support at support@PerseusSec.com. Support requests for unpaid and trial use of Perseus will be responded to during weekday business hours (Eastern Standard Time). Please contact support@PerseusSec.com if you would like to request extended or priority support.


Perseus Splunk App Components:

- Macros: Perseus creates a number of macros it uses for processing and presenting data. These are intended only for use by the application, and users are not required or expected to use these directly.
- Lookups/KV Stores: Perseus creates a number of Lookups/KV Stores it uses to store application data. These are intended only for use by the application, and users are not required or expected to use these directly.
- Python Library: Perseus creates a number of Python files it uses to provide its functionality. These are intended only for use by the application, and users are not required or expected to use these directly.
- Commands: Perseus creates a number of Python script commands it uses to update application data. These are intended only for use by the application, and users are not required or expected to use these directly.
- Scheduled Searches: Perseus creates a number of Scheduled Searches that initiate the commands above to keep application data up-to-date. These are intended only for use by the application, and users are not required or expected to use these directly.
- REST Endpoints: Perseus optionally creates a number of REST Endpoints that can be used for automating acquisition execution and upload. These are intended only for use by the application, and users are not required or expected to use these directly.